Frank DE ANGELIS, Appellant, v. A. C. ADERHOLD, Warden of the United States Penitentiary, at Atlanta, Georgia, Appellee. No. 6539. Circuit Court of Appeals, Fifth Circuit. Oct. 15, 1932. Prank De Angelis, in pro. per. Clint W. Hager, U. S. Atty., and Hal Lindsay, Asst. U. S. Atty., both of Atlanta, Ga., for appellee.

Before BRYAN, SIBLEY, and WALKER, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

The judgment is affirmed.
